# Cover Note — Offer: AI Intern (Omninuera)

This cover note lists assumptions, placeholders, and fields to be completed in the offer letter `offer_AI_intern_Omninuera.md`.

Placeholders to be filled before finalizing:
- [CANDIDATE_NAME] — Full legal name of the candidate.  
- [CANDIDATE_ADDRESS] — Candidate mailing address (optional for remote internships).  
- [CANDIDATE_EMAIL] — Candidate email address.  
- [OFFER_DATE] — Date the offer is issued.  
- [START_DATE] — Agreed internship start date (to be mutually agreed).  
- [PROBATION_PERIOD_DAYS] — If applicable, enter number of days/weeks for initial evaluation (suggest 14–30 days or leave blank if not used).  
- [IMMEDIATE_MANAGER_NAME] — Name of the reporting manager.  
- [IMMEDIATE_MANAGER_TITLE] — Title of reporting manager.  
- [HR_NAME] — HR representative name for signature.  
- [HR_TITLE] — HR representative title.  
- [HR_EMAIL] — HR contact email for acceptance and queries.  
- [HR_PHONE] — HR contact phone number (optional).  
- [OFFER_EXPIRY_DATE] — Date by which candidate should accept the offer (optional).  
- [OFFER_ACCEPTANCE_INSTRUCTIONS] — Any additional instructions for returning signed offer or required documents.

Assumptions made in this draft:
- Internship length is fixed at 3 months starting from an agreed start date.  
- Stipend is INR 10,000 per month, paid monthly.  
- Work is fully remote; candidate is based in Bengaluru for jurisdiction reference.  
- Typical weekly hours are estimated at 20–40 hours/week; exact schedule to be set by manager.  
- The company’s standard confidentiality and IP agreements will be used; the candidate will sign any required documents separately.  
- Background checks are conditional and will be communicated to the candidate if required.

Action items before final issue:
- Confirm and insert actual start date and offer expiry date.  
- Confirm probation period wording and notice periods for termination (if you wish to specify exact days).  
- Attach or link standalone confidentiality/NDA and IP assignment form if separate signature is required.  
- Confirm HR contact details and manager details.  
- Decide whether any additional benefits or reimbursements will be provided to the intern and document them.

Notes:
- This cover note is not part of the offer letter to the candidate; it is intended for internal HR use to ensure all placeholders are completed prior to sending the offer to the candidate.  
- Do not include legal advice in the final candidate-facing letter. If legal review is required, send this draft to Legal and apply their requested changes as per established workflow.

